parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of Toyota Motor Corps to provide GPS data can hinder the ability to locate a missing vehicle, potentially putting the driver and others at risk.
symptoms: Difficulty in obtaining GPS data from the vehicle manufacturer
lack of cooperation from the manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden opening of the rear hatch door can cause injury to occupants, especially if they are struck by the door.
The failure of the VSS can cause the vehicle to lose traction and control, especially in slippery or inclement conditions, which can lead to accidents.
The sudden shattering of the sunroof glass can cause injury to occupants, especially if they are struck by the glass.
The sudden and unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, especially if the brakes are unable to stop the vehicle.
symptoms: brakes are unable to stop the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to unpredictable and potentially dangerous stopping behavior, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes lock up or become difficult to stop the vehicle
the brake system warning light is illuminated
the master maintenance warning light is on
"Check ABS" and "Brake system malfunction" warning messages appear on the dashboard
chirping sound when starting the car
the car moves backward out of control when shifting into reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The noise from the regenerative system can be a sign of a larger issue, potentially leading to brake malfunction and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Barking noise when pressing the brakes
even when the engine is not on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or even death in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy or may deploy unnecessarily, causing harm to occupants.
symptoms: airbags fail to deploy in a crash
